METHOD In a large bowl, combine the pumpkin puree, sweetened condensed milk, milk, spices. and salt. In a separate bowl, whip the heavy cream until it reaches soft peak. Fold the cream gently into pumpkin mixture, then transfer to a shallow freezable container. Cover with plastic wrap or waxed paper directly on the surface of the ice cream, and place it in the freezer for 6 hours. Scoop and serve with caramel sauce, dried fruit compote, toasted pumpkin-seed brittle, or whipped cream, and a grating of nutmeg.